A former Nigerian Minister and Senator, Jubril Martins-Kuye is dead. Martins-Kuye was said to have died on Sunday morning at his Ago-Iwoye residence in Ogun State. The octogenarian was a grassroots politician who became a Senator during the third republic. The current Senator representing Ogun East, Lekan Mustapha confirmed the demise of Martins-Kuye. Senator Mustapha described the death of the elder statesman as a big blow to Ogun and Nigeria, saying, “he was a mentor and a pathfinder.” Martins-Kuye clocked 80 on August 16, 2020 and was celebrated by many, including President Muhammadu Buhari. He was appointed the Nigerian Minister of Commerce and Industry on April 6, 2010.